description: Recently sold: $121,510.

Recently sold: $410,000. For sale by owner - may be reached at 678-360-9660. This is the perfect family home located on 12.58 acres just 3 minutes from downtown Moose Lake. The house sits along a beautiful creek that emerges from the forest and runs through the backyard. Multiple trails are scattered across the property that can be used for hiking, snowshoeing, and skiing. Two separate fenced areas are located on the property. In the backyard is a fenced, raised-bed garden constructed of reclaimed barn wood. Behind the large detached garage is a fenced in orchard and chicken coop. In addition to the detached garage is a large heated attached garage. 

The house was built in 2008. Since that time, all kitchen appliances have been upgraded to top-of-the line KitchenAid stainless steel products. Floor on the main level was upgraded to rustic hardwood in 2018. 

Other features of this home include: 
- Direct access to the Soo Line and Munger trails. 
- Oversized, attached, finished garage with in-floor heat, drain, and utility tub. 
- Detached 26 foot X  30 foot second garage with 200 amp electricity
- Energy Wise certified home
- GeoThermal heating and cooling 
- Jotul high efficiency wood burning stove in the great room
- Granite kitchen counter tops
- Knotty alder cabinets, trim and doors
- Walk-out basement with large family/rec room wired with 5 in-wall/ceiling surround sound speakers
- Third floor master suite with office and loft. Large walk-in closest with his and hers sides and laundry chute. Vaulted ceiling bedroom with large bathroom and slate walk-in shower. 
- 30 foot x 9 foot Tigerwood deck
- Underground six-zone programmable irrigation sprinkler system
- Underground 2 acre electric dog fence (collar included)
- Private well and connection to city sewer
- 800 foot cement driveway with circle drive
- Kids jungle gym in wood mulched area
- In-ground adjustable basketball hoop

Recently sold: $296,030. Built in 2009, this three plus bedroom, two bath passive solar based design offers inspiring spaces and an exceptional amount of outdoor space. The living room features vaulted ceilings, lovely views from all areas of the house, and an energy efficient Lopi wood burning stove, while the modern design kitchen boasts a Silestone island with an additional sink and stainless steel appliances. The kitchen opens out to an outdoor patio that overlooks the backyard with a park like private setting. Fruit trees, berries and perennials surround the 2.5 acres. Two car detached garage with lots of storage upstairs. Pole shed with lean-to for additional storage. 
Located 3 miles from Moose Lake, and 2.5 miles to Moose Lake Public School. Close to the Munger Trail and snowmobile trails.

description: Recently sold: $315,000. Welcome to this sunshine filled home tucked away on over 7 acres of privacy! Open floorplan perfect for easy living and entertaining. Gorgeous kitchen with hickory cabinets & breakfast bar, woodburning fireplace & main floor bedroom & bath. Spacious dining area with sliding doors that lead to a beautifully landscaped yard with patio & gazebo. Great master suite, fun family room & cozy den. Tastefully decorated throughout!

Recently sold: $355,000. Very nice 2+ bedroom rambler on Island lake. House was rebuilt & enlarged in 2005. Gradual slope to the water with just a few comfy steps. Awesome lake frontage & gorgeous views with 180ft of sandy lakeshore. Big lot about 1.26ac. Partial finished walkout basement. On the main level you will have a specious entry that leads you to a large open living room with beautiful gas fire place. Nice size modern kitchen with granite counters and good amount of cupboards, brand new dishwasher, breakfast bar. It opens to a dining area and another family sitting area which walks out to a big deck facing the lake. Semi open floor plan! Also on the main level there is a big master bedroom with a double closet. It connects to a master full bathroom with double sinks. 2nd nice size bedroom, office area, another 3/4 bath with a brand new shower stall. On the lower level you will have a recreational room with a bar area and a sleeping area. Also there is an unfinished potential bathroom with some plumbing and more storage space. Forced air propane heat and central air.

House has an unfinished part of the basement too where you will have washer and dryer and more storage space. Maintenance free vinyl siding on the house and garage. Garage is 24x24, storage shed for all your extra toys. New roof shingles will be installed on house, garage, shed in September. Regular compliant septic system and a drilled well. Very private setting! Property is located on a brand new blacktop public road. Island lake is about 526 ac in size with a maximum depth of about 42ft. It's a great fishing and recreational lake. It's located close to shopping, dining, medical and it's only about 1,5hr from the metro area. Feel free to call with any questions or if you would like to preview this property
